A Kenyan science teacher has been crowned the best in the world after winning the 2019 Global Teacher Prize. Mr Peter Tabichi, a teacher at Keriko Mixed Day Secondary School in Pwani Village in Nakuru, won the $1m prize on Sunday. “It is unbelievable. I owe it all to God. I am very grateful to the almighty God,’’ these were the words of the 36-year-old Egerton University graduate when he spoke to the Nation on phone. Mr Tabichi has been a teacher for 12 years. Finalists were selected from over 10,000 nominees and applications from 179 countries around the world. More follows.   Peter Tabichi is a teacher of mathematics and science at Keriko Mixed Day Secondary School.